-- Macau casino shares slide amid crackdown on illegal payment channels
-- 
-- Wed May 07, 2014 10:15PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 8 (Reuters) - Macau casino stocks slid on Thursday after China's state-backed UnionPay announced fresh measures to crack down on illegal payment channels in the world's largest gambling hub.

Shares in Galaxy Entertainment Group Ltd <0027.HK> and Sands China Ltd <1928.HK> fell more than 5 percent, while Wynn Macau Ltd <1128.HK> dropped 6 percent and Melco Crown <6883.HK> slid 4 percent. The benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI> was up 0.3 percent at 0205 GMT. UnionPay said in a statement it was introducing new measures in Macau to combat the use of illegal credit cards and to crack down on money laundering.